text: Titan Lake In-situ Sampling Propelled Explorer (TALISE) is a proposal (or idea) about a (specific) space probe. Titan Lake In-situ Sampling Propelled Explorer (TALISE) is a proposed space probe. It was presented at the European Planetary Science Congress on September 27, 2012. If this space probe is accepted, it will be sent to Ligeia Mare, a lake on Saturn's biggest moon named Titan. It's purpose is to study the liquid on the moon and take scientific measurements while it sails to the coast. ==References== Category:Saturn Category:Moons Category:Spacecraft
